<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: CrackerJak</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-13 19:47:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Looking at the str 150 + 15 = 165  or 10%<BR>
<BR>
so a 10% raise in str for a warrior is tiny So What!<BR>
<BR>
Ever occur that us Rogues and Bards aren't that strong?<BR>
<BR>
ie  str 75 + 15 = 90   a 20% improvement!<BR>
<BR>
that 20% makes a huge difference in a Rogues Backstab <BR>
and since we can't tank or heal or cast, Backstab is<BR>
basically our bread and butter. At least until we get<BR>
make and use poison. <BR>
<BR>
Bottom line, Warriors Start strong for a reason they really don't need more strength. What They need is most likely is Dex Agi and or Cha (for taunt). Rogues and Bards Start out nimble but lack the Str and Sta and this is a perfect item <BR>
for us. <BR>
<BR>
One more note, Support your local Rogue. Too many times my fellow Rogues and I have been turned away from groups. this makes no sense. If your running away from a mob its great to have a rogue backstabbing them. We can certainly turn a rout into a victory with a few holes to an enemies spine :)</font></td></tr></table>
