<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bait</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-05 18:06:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>FBSS vs TBB is an old debate which I would like to add my 3 coppers to.<BR>
1) Conventional wisdom is that high level warriors can't solo.  With an FBSS, decent gear, and bandages (so fights start at half life) my war HAS been able to solo low blues from level 43 to 48.  Not as exciting or safe as group hunting, but the exp was better than nothing while waiting on a list.<BR>
2) Warriors are not the primary damage dealers, that is true... in short fights.  The longer the fight, or the quicker the pulls, the more melee class damage output is relied on.  Untoward/unplanned events, like being trained, mistimed pops, or wandering patrols, also rely on melee damage to win the fight.  This is all because a nuker's mana is finite.  (I digress here, but if I double hit for 120, how long does it take to equal ice comet?). ;P   Enchanters and bards are great, but not always available, esp. in pick-up groups.  <BR>
3) I have long ago maxxed out my weapon skills.  While mobs continue to get tougher, my fighting abilities are stagnating.  The only way to increase my atk is by raising strength (or buffs).  It may only be a marginal increase, but far better than nothing.  Also, this is unconfirmed (and certainly has less impact than relative level) but atk reduces the agro-radius of mobs, making pulling singles that much easier.  Although, high level warriors are called on less and less to pull, in favor of monks, and even paladins.<BR>
Have I cleared up anything? Not really, just adding more bait to the discussion.  But, which is better may depend on what situation you find yourself in.  8) <BR>
Taur-mir, war48, Bertox<BR>
P.S. ok, just thought of a 4th copper.  Attacking faster helps with the taunt factor.</font></td></tr></table>
